Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:01.64,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.29,0:00:05.06,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No matter what, I'll always be your partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.24,0:00:07.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A man of strict rules and an easygoing woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.41,0:00:09.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A tragedy happens between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.20,0:00:10.56,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeing nothing but the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:12.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}while having the body of a child:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.24,0:00:14.29,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is Detective Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.97,0:02:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are we really going to see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.92,0:02:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's for you, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.13,0:02:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's one way to put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.30,0:02:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We learned about that man yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.08,0:02:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it doesn't go in there, Kojima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.60,0:02:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Oops... Non-combustible waste goes to...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.53,0:02:27.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Learn how to separate the trash better, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.61,0:02:30.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l-Idiot, I was just a little careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.62,0:02:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're always a little careless, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.41,0:02:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah.. Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.83,0:02:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw you, he'd give a thirty minutes lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.63,0:02:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.63,0:02:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man that lives in our apartment complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.10,0:02:46.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Chiharu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} lives in an apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.30,0:02:51.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yea. His name is Iwata Iwao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.\NHe moved in about three months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.94,0:02:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's very strict about taking out trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.90,0:03:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the trash truck isn't coming, he's taking the trash back to the owner to tell them they should follow the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't he going a little bit overboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.62,0:03:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just serious about the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.62,0:03:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he's a very admirable person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.76,0:03:15.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, I wouldn't go that far...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.63,0:03:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! Why don't we all take a school trip\Nto this Iwata Iwao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} tomorrow morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.81,0:03:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A school trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.60,0:03:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you can take this strict person as your role model, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh..?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.11,0:03:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hehe... Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.90,0:03:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, we came to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.11,0:03:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Goodmorning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.32,0:03:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Goodmorning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.62,0:03:40.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's Iwata Iwao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.62,0:03:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is yours, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.12,0:03:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was some of your mail inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.13,0:03:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't peep in other people's trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.13,0:03:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's wet from the rain, so that indicates you put it outside last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.00,0:03:53.12,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Iwato Iwao (30)\N{\fs15} Machine brand research\Nestablishment employee
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.13,0:03:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The trash is to be brought in the morning!\NWhy won't you follow the rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.93,0:03:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person is just like Chiharu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.61,0:04:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mysterious overly-serious rule-follower.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.11,0:04:10.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On top of that, trash and empty cans were mixed and matched!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.62,0:04:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please separate them properly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.33,0:04:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This seems like a big spectacle, somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.50,0:04:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though people are watching...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.00,0:04:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It just means that he's serious about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.96,0:04:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.64,0:04:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:32.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be careful you, acting so great will bring you to your end someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.61,0:04:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are my classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.63,0:04:42.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Goodmorning!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.62,0:04:43.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.62,0:04:49.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've learned a lot from watching you,\Nit's good to be strict with the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.62,0:04:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No... Someone just has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.33,0:04:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.63,0:05:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he could have just quietly said it to him in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.01,0:05:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no real reason to make an uproar in front of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.60,0:05:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, there is a reason why Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is so strict with the rules...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.82,0:05:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.40,0:05:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not too soon after Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had moved in,\Nthere was an arson attempt!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.31,0:05:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arson?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.62,0:05:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone hadn't followed the rules and their garbage was set on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.42,0:05:32.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a good thing that Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} coincidentally\Nwent by and extinguished the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what you're saying is that that's the reason\Nwhy he became strict with garbage?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.10,0:05:46.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you know, if you nag people about it too much, they\Nwill just want you to shut up and won't like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's called unjustified resentment through\Nmisunderstanding, right Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.65,0:05:51.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.35,0:05:53.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Ye.. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.62,0:05:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, three days later, a case occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:05:58.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.99,0:06:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yea, Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.24,0:06:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I said about grudges!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.80,0:06:06.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I would have thought... Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.64,0:06:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Poor guy... And he was so diligent...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.60,0:06:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's the opposite!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:14.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the aggressor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.11,0:06:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man was?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.62,0:06:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.62,0:06:29.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, everyone. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.62,0:06:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually about Iwata Iwao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... Is it really true?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.27,0:06:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you guys know about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.46,0:06:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's why... Please tell us more, in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.14,0:06:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true. He really did murder someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.43,0:06:45.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A female, because she didn't deliver her trash right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.60,0:06:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For trash misdelivery?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.81,0:06:49.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For trash misdelivery?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.90,0:06:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night, I mean, around 5:30 in the morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:07:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...I woke up thirsty and while drinking\NI incidentally looked out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.12,0:07:05.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a person taking out her trash. I couldn't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.63,0:07:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You again! I told you not to take it out at night! Like previously!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.63,0:07:12.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I warned her, she...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.64,0:07:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh shut up, you're always complaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.60,0:07:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so stuck up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.94,0:07:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She suddenly tried to hit me with an iron pipe that was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.26,0:07:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even before I couldn't stand you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.56,0:07:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Like this I will get killed, I have to\Ntake that iron pipe" is what i thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.62,0:07:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.63,0:07:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He- Hey... Hey!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.63,0:07:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.63,0:07:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, he soon came to give a confession to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.14,0:07:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, instead of a case...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.60,0:07:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm.. That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.10,0:07:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I admit that I have done something unforgivable... But\Nofficer! Even though it's evil, it was in self-defence!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.32,0:07:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. It was self-defence!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.16,0:08:01.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told the truth, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.03,0:08:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Self-centered, err... defence? What will happen to that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.62,0:08:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder isn't his fault, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.83,0:08:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't his fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.63,0:08:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for it to happen in the late night...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.63,0:08:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are searching for a witness, but we really can't seem to find one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.64,0:08:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefor, it will be hard to prove if the victim\Nattacked him with an iron pipe or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you doubting him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.02,0:08:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't just take his word for it, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.61,0:08:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's only one side of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.43,0:08:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man is a very serious person!\NHe isn't someone who tells lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:40.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if he really felt threatened by her, why didn't he run?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.63,0:08:47.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bothers me too...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.75,0:08:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're getting misunderstood or mistaken,\Nthen running away would be more strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.97,0:08:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, logically thinking, yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.60,0:08:57.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the victim was always loose about taking out her trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.23,0:08:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman who passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.33,0:09:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.52,0:09:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She lived by herself in that mansion;\NKatayama Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.61,0:09:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a slack hostess, so that's why\Nshe always came home late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.04,0:09:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From our quick search, it seems that\Nshe always took out her trash at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.63,0:09:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The head of the neighbourhood association\Nalso gave her a warning, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.64,0:09:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Katayama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. If you can't follow the rules, it will be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.43,0:09:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rules, rules, that's so annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.10,0:09:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm only taking out the trash at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.60,0:09:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's such a problem, call the police to get me arrested. Humph!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.11,0:09:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that was all the head of the neighbourhood association did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.11,0:09:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that time, Iwata moved in and warned\Nher numerous times about the garbage...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.62,0:09:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...but Katayama Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} seemed very disagreeable towards Iwata.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.62,0:09:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then happened what Iwata told us, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.96,0:10:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For an easygoing woman and a rule-abiding man to be living\Nin the same neighbourhood and for this to happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.14,0:10:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a scary coincidence, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.60,0:10:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For now we can only rely on his testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.90,0:10:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So let's check out if Iwata is a reliable man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.91,0:10:17.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has only been three months since he moved here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.62,0:10:19.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's find out what happened before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.83,0:10:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll continue searching eyewitnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.13,0:10:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we clearly tell them how diligent Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.63,0:10:30.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...then we should be able to prove it was self-defence!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.64,0:10:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it really was self-defence, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.60,0:10:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if I tell you not to, you will still follow me, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.10,0:10:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s characteristics?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.11,0:10:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, did he usually make up lies?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.11,0:10:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no! For Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to tell lies? It's the opposite!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.82,0:10:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a very honest person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.12,0:10:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? This is a waste of time, Officer Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.91,0:10:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yea...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:11:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, if there was a rule-breaker here,\Nhe would likely confront him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.13,0:11:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Confront him? Nothing like that! He was a nice man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.43,0:11:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds a little different, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.81,0:11:13.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because last time we saw him, he was making a huge spectacle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.60,0:11:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yea...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.11,0:11:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he moved into that apartment, did his personality change?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.32,0:11:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah... I was surprised of his moving, because it came so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.70,0:11:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suddenly?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.12,0:11:33.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He made a contract for two years for this mansion,\Nbut in the end didn't keep it, since he moved out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.63,0:11:34.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.63,0:11:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So are you saying that he had plans continuing living here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.93,0:11:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...but he suddenly changed his mind and moved\Nto that apartment in the Beika area?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.23,0:11:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} moved to the Beika area?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.40,0:11:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.. What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.82,0:11:55.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing... But moving to a smaller apartment...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.11,0:12:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't have any money problems and\Nhis company was quite close from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.12,0:12:02.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was much more convenient, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.42,0:12:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three months ago, there might have been some sudden\Nreason for him to necessarily move to that apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.63,0:12:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yea..
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.63,0:12:12.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't think of anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.01,0:12:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And because he moved, the case occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.85,0:12:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what does that mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.81,0:12:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.60,0:12:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.61,0:12:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you ask me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.82,0:12:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, this case wasn't coincidental!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.11,0:12:28.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.00,0:12:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three months ago, you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.33,0:12:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, did something different happen to Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.63,0:12:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.80,0:12:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! For such a bright guy, he was unexpectedly\Nwearing a very cold expression about that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.10,0:12:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it after his grave visit...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.02,0:12:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grave visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.23,0:12:59.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes... It was the second anniversary of his benefactor's\Ndeath who took care of him when he was in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.32,0:13:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The grave visit, was it before he moved to the apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.62,0:13:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think it was soon after he moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.33,0:13:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That grave visit might have something to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.50,0:13:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,School-time benefactors...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.63,0:13:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you must mean Yasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.44,0:13:17.05,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ikami Lawyer Office\NBetter than good law-office
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.22,0:13:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iwata and I were both broke and schooling,...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.60,0:13:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...with part-time jobs, we made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.10,0:13:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His part-time job was with Yasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had a workshop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.52,0:13:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wife threated the parentless\NIwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} like their own son.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.95,0:13:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even when he got in an accident near the\Nworkplace and was injured badly...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.12,0:13:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a blood transfusion is necassary, please use my blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.83,0:13:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mine too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.50,0:13:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seemed the couple became his lifeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.51,0:13:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that couple were life donors, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.51,0:13:53.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iwata said the same thing, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.43,0:14:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...two years ago, the poor couple was deceived by a money-lender\Nand their house and even the workshop were taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.61,0:14:03.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They commited suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.40,0:14:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that grave visit, it must have been\Nexactly 2 years ago since that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.83,0:14:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, the grave was in\NHenryuuji, somewhere in the Beika area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.63,0:14:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Henryuuji is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.50,0:14:21.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's close to Chiharu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} s apartment, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.89,0:14:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.30,0:14:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait... From Beika Station to those apartments.\NIt's right after them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.10,0:14:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that moneylender who deceived the couple\Nand drove them to suicide is now...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.40,0:14:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should be in prison already, he was guilty on many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.32,0:14:42.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.33,0:14:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.91,0:14:47.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a woman involved in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.71,0:14:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I researched a bit, I leared that the Fujikura\Nlender was introduced by this woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.24,0:14:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found out that she knew from the beginning that it was all a sceam.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.24,0:15:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any way for that woman to take responsability as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.23,0:15:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she only introduced them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.60,0:15:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunatly, she can't be punished by law.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.61,0:15:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't be punished by law... That woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.28,0:15:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Iwata was in agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.45,0:15:17.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that woman's name was...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.37,0:15:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't heard, but she was working\Nin some bar or club as a hostess.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.12,0:15:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.63,0:15:25.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.46,0:15:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.72,0:15:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would like to quickly confirm\Nsomething about a convicted Fujikura...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.73,0:15:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.73,0:15:41.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He died of an illness last month?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.03,0:15:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fujikura?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.24,0:15:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fujikura Eiji. Have you heard from the name Katayama Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.70,0:15:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't know with what kind of men that\Nunpleasant woman would go out with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.13,0:15:59.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but they worked together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.01,0:16:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.48,0:16:13.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.11,0:16:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! About the previous... You made sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.53,0:16:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.32,0:16:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the prison guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's heard about the person working with Fujikura.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.62,0:16:32.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fujikura said himself, that once we would be out, he was going\Nto meet a hostess named Misa to hurt people again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.13,0:16:35.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're connected. The victim and the assailant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.13,0:16:36.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mutsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.72,0:16:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there isn't any decisive evidence yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.51,0:16:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.52,0:16:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Co- Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.02,0:16:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with this kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.03,0:16:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.11,0:16:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This person is Katayama Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:17:00.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.62,0:17:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this a recent picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.62,0:17:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About six months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.13,0:17:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Six months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.42,0:17:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there something wrong with this picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.63,0:17:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.01,0:17:20.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. She left it between a car door, they were almost\Ntorn off. It was a big mess. They were all fine but one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.11,0:17:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All but one...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.11,0:17:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have one thing I want to confirm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.45,0:17:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The weapon we have as evidence,\Nabout that particular iron pipe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.62,0:17:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We left to find the evidence to help Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nbut only confirmed an unbelievable thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.80,0:17:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.01,0:17:45.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The result is clear, because there is only one truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.80,0:17:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You do know why we asked you here, don't you, Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.52,0:17:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From this point, three months ago, you came here to visit this grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.32,0:18:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This grave is Yasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s who commited suicide two years ago after\Nbeing deceived by an evil-mannered money-loaner named Fujikura Eiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.12,0:18:06.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You came to see them then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.37,0:18:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.00,0:18:16.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that grave visit, as you were heading back\Nto the train station, you accidently saw her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.14,0:18:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was the woman who worked with Fujikura\NEiji in deceiving the Yasaka couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.52,0:18:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rules, rules! That's so annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.81,0:18:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm only taking the trash out at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.90,0:18:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you have a problem, call the cops to have me arrested!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.11,0:18:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if she had driven the virtuous couple\Nto suicide, she wasn't regretting it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.41,0:18:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That time, you thought about it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.83,0:18:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For you to have met her again was certainly fate, a chance\Nto seek revenge for the generous Yasaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.22,0:18:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You rent a room for a place right across hers and moved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.52,0:19:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you were seeking revenge, you didn't want to be caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.43,0:19:09.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since she hadn't gotten any punishment by law, the revenge wasn't\Nyour sin. So you thought of a way to kill her in self-defence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.53,0:19:13.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You innitiated your plan immediatly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.41,0:19:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You started the arson fear, which became your excuse of becoming\Na very strict man about disposal and warning people about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.72,0:19:24.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you only had to wait for your chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.43,0:19:30.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You continued to wait for that woman, Katayama\NMisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, to bring her garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.93,0:19:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, you were waiting for the ideal chance\Nwhen nobody would be passing by.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.53,0:19:42.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, last night, that chance finally came.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.42,0:20:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You pressed her fingerprints on the iron pipe\Nyou had prepared and reported to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.52,0:20:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so, Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.43,0:20:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make a planned murder look like an accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.02,0:20:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it would look only like some neighbourhood problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.32,0:20:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought that the police wouldn't search\Ntoo much about the participants' past, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.12,0:20:26.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That woman... picked up an iron pipe that was\Nleft behind and suddenly tried to hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.63,0:20:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was only protecting myself! That was only self-defence!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.93,0:20:32.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.22,0:20:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.22,0:20:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.60,0:20:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have proof. Katayama Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.31,0:20:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fingerprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.02,0:20:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that woman's fingerprints weren't on the iron pipe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.74,0:20:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, we found both of her hands. All ten fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.58,0:21:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Six months ago, Katayama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} injured her right index\Nfinger badly. After that she couldn't bend it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.92,0:21:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone must've forcefully pressed her fingers to the iron\Npipe, otherwise that finger's fingerprint wouldn't be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.11,0:21:17.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't forgive her! That woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.90,0:21:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for the blood, I wouldn't have survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.53,0:21:26.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, if you look away, you will get hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.54,0:21:31.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! I was thinking that maybe you would let me\Nwork here after I graduate from High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.50,0:21:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't say stupid things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.50,0:21:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Iwata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. You will become\Nthe ruler in Japan, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.72,0:21:41.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! Not only of Japan, but of the whole world!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.10,0:21:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true. Hahaha!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.73,0:21:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To deceive such a nice couple... I couldn't rest\Nwith it, even if I had to commit a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.40,0:21:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what you did is still a crime. No matter\Nhow unforgivable of an opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.70,0:22:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way to fix it with an apology!
